        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Hehe.. this happened to me in Trakanons Teeth... was camping with a chanter friend near some of the spectral keepers (left of EJ zone) when we decided to header over to the swamp zone (trying to get forager)..</P><P>Took a while before it occured to me that maybe I left the pet guarding our camping spot :)</P><P>As for the sarnak fortress.. there isn't much in the way of pathing there.. so pets try to get to you in a straight line, and if they try to go somewhere but don't actually move for a while (ie walking into walls) they teleport.  However, unlike other NPCs that are trying to get at you, pets don't teleport on top of you (don't know where they do teleport to.. maybe 0,0 or something).. I first discovered this in Najena, when my pet couldn't fit through doors anymore. </P><P></P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
